Roasted Salmon and Ratatouille with couscous

Veg-filled ratatouille makes the perfect base for rich and flaky roasted salmon. Warm
and fluffy couscous adds a filling factor to make this a dish that's healthy and
hearty in equal measure.

Preheat the oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

In a #pot{} for the couscous boil @water{200%ml} (double for 4p). Add half the
@vegetable stock{1/2%sachet}.

Trim the @aubergine{1} and halve lengthways. Chop each half into four strips and
chop into 2cm pieces. Toss with a little @oil{} and season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

Arrange in one layer on a lined #baking tray{}. Roast until soft, ~{20-25%mins}.
Turn halfway through.

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

Meanwhile, halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into
2cm chunks.

Peel and grate the @garlic{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Remove the stock from the heat, stir in the @couscous{100%g} and pop a lid on the
#pot{}.

Leave to the side for ~{8-10%mins} or until ready to serve.

Lay the @salmon{200%g} fillets, skin-side down, onto a lined baking tray.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

When the oven is hot, roast the salmon on the top shelf until cooked through,
~{10-15%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: The salmon is cooked when opaque in the middle.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #pan{} on medium-high heat and add the pepper. Fry
until softened, stirring occasionally, ~{4-5%mins}.

Add the garlic and stir together. Cook for ~{1%min}.

Add the @Italian herbs{1%sachet}, @passata{1%pack}, remaining
@vegetable stock{1/2%sachet} and @water{100%ml} (double for 4p). Stir together and
simmer until reduced slightly, ~{3-4%mins}.

Once cooked, stir in the roasted aubergine. Season to taste with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

Fluff up the couscous with a #fork{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} to taste.

Divide the couscous between plates and spoon over the ratatouille.

Place the roasted salmon on top.